WEBVTT

00:48.917 --> 00:49.917
Come on, Bro.

01:13.917 --> 01:14.999
Hey, watch it.

01:15.000 --> 01:16.832
You were in my way, Bro.

01:16.833 --> 01:18.333
Oh, okay.

01:34.042 --> 01:35.499
Is that all you got?

01:35.500 --> 01:37.625
You want to go faster, huh?

01:54.125 --> 01:55.458
That was cool, Bro.

01:56.500 --> 01:57.708
<i>Skxawng</i>, let go.

02:01.000 --> 02:02.332
It was cool riding
with you, Bro.

02:02.333 --> 02:03.625
High four.

02:11.958 --> 02:13.625
All right,
I got to get back, Bro.

02:14.458 --> 02:15.708
Little Brother,

02:16.333 --> 02:18.333
tell me one thing
before you go.

02:20.958 --> 02:22.167
How did I die?

02:28.833 --> 02:30.292
You got shot.

02:31.833 --> 02:34.000
We could have escaped, but I
made us go back for Spider.

02:35.208 --> 02:36.542
Then we had to go back.

02:37.333 --> 02:38.416
That's not your fault.

02:38.417 --> 02:39.583
Tell that to Dad.

02:40.167 --> 02:42.250
We weren't even supposed
to be out there.

02:43.667 --> 02:46.582
I got us caught
because I disobeyed orders.

02:46.583 --> 02:48.375
That's just you, Little Bro.

02:58.792 --> 03:00.167
I love you, Brother.

03:00.792 --> 03:01.458
<i>Skxawng.</i>

03:07.708 --> 03:09.292
<i>I killed my brother.</i>

03:10.167 --> 03:11.375
<i>No matter what happens,</i>

03:12.125 --> 03:15.500
<i>I have to live with that
for the rest of my life.</i>

03:54.000 --> 03:55.083
I wish I could do it.

03:55.625 --> 03:57.667
No, I wish I could do it.

03:59.417 --> 04:02.041
If I have another
stupid seizure underwater...

04:02.042 --> 04:03.124
Yeah,

04:03.125 --> 04:04.875
you'd be me
without a mask.

04:07.292 --> 04:08.707
- Let's test that.
- Hey, hey.

04:08.708 --> 04:10.249
- Watch it.
- See what happens.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.375
Hey, watch the stitches.

04:12.500 --> 04:14.374
Uh-huh. Yeah,
how do you like that, huh?

04:14.375 --> 04:15.375
No!

04:38.250 --> 04:39.916
<i>The fire of hate</i>

04:39.917 --> 04:41.792
<i>leaves only
the ash of grief.</i>

04:43.750 --> 04:45.166
<i>My mother mourned</i>

04:45.167 --> 04:46.250
<i>the ancient way,</i>

04:46.792 --> 04:49.333
<i>singing her son's life
during the daily eclipse.</i>

04:51.250 --> 04:53.125
<i>Because the light
always returns.</i>

05:02.667 --> 05:03.792
<i>There's the</i> Na'vi <i>way,</i>

05:04.792 --> 05:06.292
<i>and then there's
my dad's way.</i>

05:07.000 --> 05:09.375
<i>Say nothing.
Keep busy.</i>

05:28.208 --> 05:30.458
<i>The Reef People say
the sea washes you clean.</i>

05:31.958 --> 05:33.458
<i>Washes away your sins.</i>

06:10.500 --> 06:11.500
What do you got?

06:13.333 --> 06:14.749
You're supposed
to be collecting guns.

06:14.750 --> 06:16.208
That thing's useless.

06:16.792 --> 06:17.917
Focus, boy.

06:23.667 --> 06:25.292
Don't let your mother
see that.

06:34.333 --> 06:35.125
Hey, excuse me.

06:35.333 --> 06:36.874
- Sorry.
- Excuse me.

06:36.875 --> 06:38.000
- Tuk.
- Sorry.

06:45.083 --> 06:46.083
Bro.

06:47.708 --> 06:48.958
Ah, sick.

06:50.375 --> 06:51.375
What is this?

06:52.625 --> 06:53.625
Tsireya?

06:55.125 --> 06:56.458
What are you doing?

06:58.833 --> 07:01.374
This is an AR, all right?

07:01.375 --> 07:03.499
This is the mag.
It's where the bullets are.

07:03.500 --> 07:04.667
Empty.

07:05.583 --> 07:06.583
Slap it.

07:07.542 --> 07:08.542
Rack it.

07:09.083 --> 07:09.957
And then, boom,

07:09.958 --> 07:11.000
you can just spray.

07:11.625 --> 07:13.332
You can kill
a lot of Sky People with this.

07:13.333 --> 07:15.499
See? Ceramic action.

07:15.500 --> 07:17.624
You clean 'em and oil 'em,
be as good as new.

07:17.625 --> 07:19.707
This is not the <i>Na'vi</i> way,

07:19.708 --> 07:20.708
<i>Jakesully.</i>

07:20.917 --> 07:23.082
Weapons of metal
are forbidden.

07:23.083 --> 07:24.166
You know this.

07:24.167 --> 07:25.249
To touch them

07:25.250 --> 07:26.667
poisons the heart.

07:27.167 --> 07:28.249
Eywa

07:28.250 --> 07:29.333
will provide.

07:30.792 --> 07:31.833
Right.

07:32.875 --> 07:35.208
The mourning period
is not even over.

07:35.750 --> 07:37.624
- Tuk.
- You should be with your family,

07:37.625 --> 07:39.416
not gathering these things.

07:39.417 --> 07:40.999
Your woman

07:41.000 --> 07:42.125
needs you.

07:44.167 --> 07:47.167
My son lies with the ancestors
in the reef.

07:48.042 --> 07:49.666
This is our home.

07:49.667 --> 07:50.457
I said I would

07:50.458 --> 07:51.624
stand and fight,

07:51.625 --> 07:54.416
but I can't fight gunships
with spears.

07:54.417 --> 07:56.332
We sank the demon ship.

07:56.333 --> 07:58.083
The pink skins fear us now.

07:59.708 --> 08:01.749
Yeah? We got lucky.

08:01.750 --> 08:03.208
And they got many more ships.

08:04.000 --> 08:05.417
Least we got these.

08:06.625 --> 08:08.958
We are grateful you
stand with us, <i>Jakesully</i>.

08:09.625 --> 08:11.041
It is not guns we need.

08:11.042 --> 08:12.458
It is Rider of Last Shadow.

08:14.250 --> 08:15.957
Ride great <i>toruk</i>

08:15.958 --> 08:18.000
as you did before.

08:20.333 --> 08:22.666
When you ride the beast,

08:22.667 --> 08:24.000
you become the beast.

08:25.292 --> 08:27.375
And the more blood,
the better.

08:29.042 --> 08:30.999
I will not become

08:31.000 --> 08:32.957
<i>Toruk Makto</i> again.

08:34.000 --> 08:35.207
<i>Jakesully</i>,

08:36.167 --> 08:38.292
you are always <i>Toruk Makto.</i>

08:39.457 --> 08:41.500
Come. Rotxo.

08:47.167 --> 08:48.208
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

08:48.833 --> 08:51.125
Yeah, we can hear you
loud and clear. Go on, Doc.

08:52.042 --> 08:55.042
<i>So we've been through
the wreck, inside and out.</i>

08:55.792 --> 08:58.542
<i>We've searched to about
a 200-meter radius around it.</i>

08:59.083 --> 09:00.666
<i>We didn't find
any</i> Na'vi <i>bodies.</i>

09:00.667 --> 09:03.749
<i>Just crew or...
what's left of 'em.</i>

09:03.750 --> 09:06.124
Well, keep looking, Doctor.

09:06.125 --> 09:08.416
- Expand the search radius.
<i>- Roger that.</i>

09:08.417 --> 09:09.332
<i>Of note though,</i>

09:09.333 --> 09:11.333
<i>I did find an interesting
new algae.</i>

09:13.125 --> 09:14.624
<i>Hello? Can you hear me?</i>

09:14.625 --> 09:16.916
- Sully is still out there.
- We don't know that.

09:16.917 --> 09:19.082
Scavengers could have
carried off the bodies.

09:19.083 --> 09:21.333
Nope. He made it out.

09:21.792 --> 09:25.124
And he's in this area.
Down to a handful of villages.

09:25.125 --> 09:26.666
You just give me a ship
and I'll--

09:26.667 --> 09:27.832
I gave you a ship.

09:27.833 --> 09:29.583
It's right there,
on the bottom.

09:30.333 --> 09:31.750
Along with my crew.

09:32.583 --> 09:33.583
All dead.

09:34.583 --> 09:36.416
You brought me out here,

09:36.417 --> 09:38.541
twenty-six trillion miles,

09:38.542 --> 09:40.249
for a single mission,

09:40.250 --> 09:41.832
a kinetic hard kill op

09:41.833 --> 09:43.833
against one guy.

09:44.375 --> 09:46.292
I ain't backing off.

09:49.958 --> 09:52.042
<i>Are we still connected?
Hello?</i>

09:53.167 --> 09:54.750
<i>Do they have me on mute?</i>

10:01.667 --> 10:04.042
The spirit of my ancestors
is in this bow.

10:06.500 --> 10:07.708
It was our strength.

10:10.875 --> 10:13.333
I can help you
fix it, Lo'ak.

10:15.042 --> 10:16.042
No!

10:17.292 --> 10:18.375
It's ruined!

10:19.583 --> 10:21.583
<i>Everything I touch
gets ruined.</i>

10:26.708 --> 10:28.208
<i>They never talked about it.</i>

10:30.250 --> 10:31.708
<i>But it was there
in the room.</i>

10:32.333 --> 10:34.208
<i>Like a crouching thanator.</i>

10:37.458 --> 10:39.583
I know you will never
give up your bow.

10:41.583 --> 10:42.583
So...

10:47.458 --> 10:49.208
Just don't be close
when it hits.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.167
So, you agree with Ronal?

11:13.958 --> 11:15.916
I will never speak against
my husband

11:15.917 --> 11:17.417
in front of that woman.

11:20.042 --> 11:21.250
Look, I'm a marine.

11:23.208 --> 11:25.083
I'm not taking a knife
to a gunfight.

11:27.292 --> 11:28.417
Or a prayer.

11:31.083 --> 11:32.792
So, what am I
supposed to do?

11:33.875 --> 11:36.333
I can't run.
I can't fight.

11:36.833 --> 11:37.833
Oh, that's right.

11:38.500 --> 11:41.582
Eywa will provide. Yeah?
So, where was Eywa?

11:41.583 --> 11:43.374
Where was Eywa
when our son--

11:43.375 --> 11:44.375
Jake!

11:47.042 --> 11:49.583
I'm in this place
where I have nothing.

11:50.792 --> 11:53.417
Not my people,
not my forest.

11:54.875 --> 11:56.792
Even my father's bow
is gone.

11:59.792 --> 12:00.917
All I have...

12:02.208 --> 12:03.458
is my faith

12:04.292 --> 12:06.708
that this is
the Great Mother's plan.

12:09.667 --> 12:11.250
You have this family.

12:25.458 --> 12:26.792
And you have me.

12:29.083 --> 12:31.042
And I love you so much.

12:54.542 --> 12:56.625
Yeah, Payakan,
you're the man!

13:24.250 --> 13:24.958
Bro, Bro.

13:28.167 --> 13:29.500
This is sick!

13:45.792 --> 13:49.500
Bro, come on!
Go, go, go, go! Yeah!

13:54.625 --> 13:56.291
That was insane, cuz.

13:56.292 --> 13:57.458
I know, right, Bro?

13:59.625 --> 14:00.792
I thought you were dead.

14:04.708 --> 14:07.457
It sucks that Payakan
is still an outcast.

14:07.458 --> 14:09.332
Yeah. After saving
all our asses.

14:09.333 --> 14:11.041
No.
I'm sorry,

14:11.042 --> 14:13.250
but by the <i>tulkun</i> way,
he bears the deaths.

14:14.125 --> 14:15.542
All those
who died in the battle.

14:16.458 --> 14:17.833
He bears those deaths.

14:20.000 --> 14:20.749
I'm sorry.

14:20.750 --> 14:22.792
You saved us all.

14:29.458 --> 14:31.167
Forever, Brother.

14:31.292 --> 14:32.292
Always.

14:45.333 --> 14:46.333
Dad!

14:50.542 --> 14:52.291
- Wait, where's the spare?
- It's in the basket, I think.

14:52.292 --> 14:53.624
Hey! Wake up! Where is it?

14:53.625 --> 14:55.499
- Hey! Where's the spare mask?
- What?

14:55.500 --> 14:57.249
Where's the spare mask?
It used to be there. Where is it?

14:57.250 --> 14:58.666
- I don't know.
- Find it.

14:58.667 --> 15:00.499
- It's not here.
- Speak to me. Where is it?

15:00.500 --> 15:02.582
- I can't find it.
- Hey, hey! Where is it?

15:02.583 --> 15:04.000
- Come on. Come on. Come on.
- I got it. Dad.

15:04.542 --> 15:06.167
- Dad. I found it.
- Hurry.

15:11.375 --> 15:12.917
Spider, no.

15:13.208 --> 15:14.291
Breathe.

15:14.292 --> 15:16.249
- Breathe.
- Breathe.

15:16.250 --> 15:17.625
Deep and slow.

15:18.292 --> 15:19.458
Deep and slow.

15:19.958 --> 15:21.374
There you go.
You're okay.

15:21.375 --> 15:24.500
I'm good. I'm good.
I'm okay.

15:26.667 --> 15:28.792
<i>Skxawng.</i>
You have to be careful.

15:29.333 --> 15:30.957
- Careful's my middle name.
- Yeah, <i>skxawng.</i>

15:30.958 --> 15:33.582
- You should be more careful, little baby.
- Pay attention.

15:33.583 --> 15:36.374
- Get off. Get off. Get off.
- Stupid is your middle name.

15:36.375 --> 15:37.457
- Be careful, little baby.
- No, let him go.

15:37.458 --> 15:39.541
- Yeah, you have to pay attention.
- <i>Skxawng</i> is his middle name.

15:39.542 --> 15:41.708
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Yeah, I feel fine.

15:44.333 --> 15:46.875
The Windtraders.
The Windtraders are here.

15:48.417 --> 15:49.707
The Windtraders
are coming.

15:49.708 --> 15:50.791
Come on!

15:50.792 --> 15:51.917
Come on. Let's go.

15:52.417 --> 15:53.417
Come on.

15:54.583 --> 15:55.625
Come on, Tuk.

16:18.042 --> 16:19.042
Hey!

16:35.667 --> 16:36.667
Tsireya.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.333
Look.

16:42.917 --> 16:43.666
Look at him.

16:43.667 --> 16:45.250
He's not going
to take up much room.

16:45.958 --> 16:47.458
As long as he's no trouble.

16:48.458 --> 16:50.332
- Take a knee. Let's go. Tuk.
- Kiri.

16:50.333 --> 16:51.791
- Come on, Kiri.
- What?

16:51.792 --> 16:53.666
- Kiri, please.
- Children, please sit down.

16:53.667 --> 16:54.708
Please, sit.

16:56.208 --> 16:58.958
Your mother and I have
come to a decision.

17:04.041 --> 17:06.040
Spider, you're going to live
back in High Camp with Norm.

17:06.041 --> 17:07.790
- What?
- The Windtraders will take you.

17:07.791 --> 17:09.832
- No, Dad.
- No, Dad. He can't.

17:09.833 --> 17:13.415
Spider, you can't live in a mask
day and night.

17:13.416 --> 17:15.332
I just want
to stay here with you.

17:15.333 --> 17:18.041
- I know, but it's just too risky.
- This isn't fair.

17:18.875 --> 17:21.040
Please. You're the only family
I've ever known.

17:21.041 --> 17:22.540
This is what's best for you.

17:22.541 --> 17:24.290
But, Dad, he's our best friend.

17:24.291 --> 17:25.665
Can't we just
find a way?

17:25.666 --> 17:26.749
It's too dangerous.

17:26.750 --> 17:29.082
You're one dead battery away
from being dead yourself.

17:29.083 --> 17:31.416
He belongs
with his own kind.

17:31.417 --> 17:32.083
Mom.

17:32.708 --> 17:35.791
And what kind is that, Mother?
Alien?

17:35.792 --> 17:37.166
- Kiri.
- Pink-ass.

17:37.167 --> 17:38.249
- Kiri.
- Stop.

17:38.250 --> 17:40.708
You hate them so much,
that's all you see.

17:41.542 --> 17:42.542
It's Spider.

17:43.417 --> 17:44.707
Please, Jake.

17:44.708 --> 17:46.874
Mr. Sully, I won't be any problem.
You know that.

17:46.875 --> 17:48.082
Dad, this isn't right.

17:48.083 --> 17:50.291
Spider is part of this family.

17:50.292 --> 17:53.750
- He will never be a part of this family.
- Mother, no.

17:56.125 --> 17:58.957
The caravan is the safest way
to move him.

17:58.958 --> 18:00.499
- No, please.
- He's going today.

18:00.500 --> 18:02.541
- You can't do this. No, Dad, he's--
- It's a done deal.

18:02.542 --> 18:06.041
Enough! This is a family.
It's not a democracy.

18:06.042 --> 18:07.249
All right?

18:07.250 --> 18:09.541
- I hate you!
- This is what is best, baby girl.

18:09.542 --> 18:10.624
- No!
- Hey, it's okay.

18:10.625 --> 18:11.958
Don't touch me!

18:13.250 --> 18:14.250
It's okay.

18:15.667 --> 18:16.917
- You understand?
- No.

18:18.417 --> 18:20.000
I already lost my brother.

18:20.708 --> 18:22.208
I can't lose anyone else.

18:28.792 --> 18:30.458
<i>Sullys stick together.</i>

18:32.167 --> 18:34.375
<i>Yep, that's the family motto.</i>

18:38.292 --> 18:39.957
- It's bullshit.
- This isn't fair.

18:39.958 --> 18:41.666
Okay, okay.

18:41.667 --> 18:43.499
Hey. All right.
How about this?

18:43.500 --> 18:45.832
We all go together
to drop him off.

18:45.833 --> 18:46.500
Kiri.

18:48.208 --> 18:50.207
You said you wanted to see
your grandmother.

18:50.208 --> 18:53.792
Yeah, it will be an adventure.
For the whole family.

18:58.375 --> 19:00.083
Yeah. Cool.

19:12.917 --> 19:14.083
Hey, stay here.

19:16.750 --> 19:20.291
Our arrangement was
for the pink-skinned boy only.

19:20.292 --> 19:21.916
We won't be any trouble.

19:21.917 --> 19:23.374
You are already trouble.

19:23.375 --> 19:25.457
A trader must move freely.

19:25.458 --> 19:26.458
We cannot choose sides.

19:27.292 --> 19:29.124
Having <i>Toruk Makto</i>
on board

19:29.125 --> 19:32.333
cuts very close to
choosing a side in this war.

19:32.958 --> 19:34.707
Yeah, but you're mistaken.

19:34.708 --> 19:36.792
<i>Toruk Makto</i>
was never on your ship.

19:39.583 --> 19:41.750
But if he was ever
aboard, then...

19:43.000 --> 19:45.749
him and his woman would be
happy to fly as outriders

19:45.750 --> 19:47.167
and protect your caravan.

19:50.208 --> 19:51.333
Perhaps so.

19:52.292 --> 19:54.583
The <i>Mangkwan</i> raiders
grow more aggressive.

19:56.750 --> 19:58.625
Very well.
I meet you on this.

20:05.375 --> 20:06.667
Cast off!

20:07.958 --> 20:08.958
Come on.

20:09.083 --> 20:10.208
Cast off!

20:12.542 --> 20:14.208
Cast off below!

20:19.708 --> 20:20.542
Lo'ak!

20:20.833 --> 20:21.832
Lo'ak!

20:21.833 --> 20:23.375
Oh, Tsireya!
Tsireya!

20:23.875 --> 20:24.708
Lo'ak!

20:26.125 --> 20:27.458
Ready about!

20:28.875 --> 20:31.457
Ready about! On all lines.

20:31.458 --> 20:32.958
Bow to starboard.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.916
Windward vanes out full!

20:42.917 --> 20:45.207
Haul out and raise full to windward!

20:45.208 --> 20:46.333
Heave!

20:46.917 --> 20:47.917
Heave!

20:48.333 --> 20:49.667
Heave!

20:52.708 --> 20:53.708
Heave!

20:55.958 --> 20:58.208
Lighten ship. Come up easy.

21:05.458 --> 21:07.375
Windward out full!

21:11.292 --> 21:13.792
Make all and set taut!

21:55.167 --> 21:56.167
Yeah!

22:03.333 --> 22:05.208
<i>Everyone mourns
in their own way.</i>

22:09.208 --> 22:10.375
<i>For me,</i>

22:10.917 --> 22:12.208
<i>it's being up here alone.</i>

22:15.083 --> 22:16.833
<i>I feel him with me.</i>

22:19.333 --> 22:20.458
Bro, check it out.

22:21.083 --> 22:23.375
<i>I hear his voice in the wind.</i>

22:39.542 --> 22:40.542
Hold this.

22:50.292 --> 22:52.291
Hey, Dad, I've been thinking.

22:52.292 --> 22:53.791
I should carry a rifle.

22:53.792 --> 22:55.207
And I could fly with you.

22:55.208 --> 22:56.208
Yeah.

22:57.042 --> 22:58.541
That's gonna happen.

22:58.542 --> 23:00.082
Why not?

23:00.083 --> 23:01.666
You trained me to shoot, okay?

23:01.667 --> 23:03.167
I know what I'm doing.

23:03.708 --> 23:05.249
Yeah? Where's your comms?

23:05.250 --> 23:06.667
I called you like five times.

23:08.333 --> 23:09.958
Wear your comms.

23:10.667 --> 23:11.667
That's rule number one.

23:13.625 --> 23:14.958
You can't even do that.

23:27.167 --> 23:28.292
Bring up the next one.

23:30.333 --> 23:31.333
That's it.

23:33.958 --> 23:35.124
What you got?

23:35.125 --> 23:36.666
So, I promised this guy on imaging
a case of beer

23:36.667 --> 23:38.333
if he ever got something for us.

23:39.708 --> 23:42.791
Long-range patrols clocked these guys
when they punched our airspace.

